  "body": "it looks like the latest geth version does only reset the getWork package if a new block arrives, that might explain why we see so many blocks with a block time of 1 second. You can check it by running the following code side by side with the geth log:\n\n```\nvar web3 = require('web3');\nweb3.setProvider(new web3.providers.HttpProvider('http://localhost:8545'));\n\nupdateCurrentWork();\nfunction updateCurrentWork() {\n  web3.eth.getWork(function(error, data){\n    console.log(data[0]);\n    setTimeout(updateCurrentWork, 150);\n  });  \n}\n```\n\nThe block hash only changes when a new block is imported. But shouldn't it change from time to time as the block timestamp is updated to the current time?\n",
